Function:
In SAPUI5 Development, the terms’ function and action have different meanings on whether they refer to client side code( JavaScript) or the backend OData service definition.
Client-side (SAPUI5/JavaScript): A function is a standard JavaScript code block that performs a task or calculates a value. These are the foundational building blocks of your UI logic, used for things like handling events, formatting data, or organizing code in your controllers and utility files.
Back-End (OData Service): In an OData Service, a function is a server-side operation that must be read-only and must not have any observable side effects. Functions are invoked using HTTP GET requests and are primarily used to return data that cannot be retrieved through standard entity set queries, such as a calculated value.
Action:
Client-Side (SAPUI5/JavaScript/Fiori Elements):
An action in the UI Typically refers to a user interaction, like a button press (E.g; “save”, “delete”, “approve”) that triggers a specific behavior. These user interface actions can be built-in (generic Fiori actions), defined via annotations, or implemented with custom controller code.
Back-End OData Service:
In an OData service, an action is a server-side operation that may have side effects on the server data. Actions are designed for logic that modifies data (e.g; changing the status of an order) and are invoked using HTTP POST requests to ensure proper transactional handling and prevent non-deterministic behavior.
Call back function:
In SAPUI5 a callback function is a standard JavaScript function passed as an argument to another function, which is executed upon completion of an operation, such as event, an asynchronous data call, or dialog closing. They are essential for handling the flow of control, particularly in asynchronous scenarios like OData model operations or loading fragments.
