Capm main folder structure:
In an SAP Cloud Application Programming Model (CAPM) project, the directory structure is designed to separate concerns between the data model, service layer, and user interface. 
db/ - Database Layer
This folder contains all artifacts related to the application's persistent data structure. 
•	Data Models: Defined using Core Data Services (CDS) in files such as schema.cds or data-model.cds.
•	Entities: These definitions are converted into physical database tables or views during deployment (e.g., to SAP HANA or SQLite).
•	Initial Data: A subfolder named db/data/ typically contains .csv files used to prepopulate the database with initial configuration or master data. 
srv/ - Service Layer
This folder holds the business logic and defines how data is exposed to the outside world. 
•	Service Definitions: Managed in .cds files (e.g., cat-service.cds), these files define OData services by projecting or exposing entities from the db/ layer.
•	Business Logic: Custom behaviors and event handlers (such as before, on, or after hooks) are implemented here using JavaScript (.js) or TypeScript (.ts) files that match the service file names. 
app/ - UI Layer
This folder is dedicated to the frontend and user-facing components of the application. 
•	Web Content: Contains static assets, HTML, and UI frameworks like SAP Fiori or SAPUI5.
•	UI Annotations: Often contains fiori or annotations.cds files that define how the data should be rendered in standard SAP Fiori elements.
•	Application Router: In complex deployments, this folder may also house configuration for the Application Router to manage authentication and routing between the UI and backend

